################################################################################
# Optimized .vscodeignore
# Only excludes files not needed in the published VS Code extension package.
# Assumes you run `vsce package` from the `vscode-extension/` directory.
################################################################################

# Editor & test harness folders
.vscode/**
.vscode-test/**

# Source TypeScript (we ship compiled JS in lib/)
src/**
**/*.ts
**/*.map

# Tests & coverage artifacts
test/**
tests/**
**/*.test.*
**/*.spec.*
coverage/**
.nyc_output/**

# Node dev dependencies that are not bundled (vsce will include prod deps automatically)
node_modules/**

# Git / CI metadata
.git/**
.github/**

# Build & config files not required at runtime
tsconfig.json
tsconfig.test.json
*.tsbuildinfo
eslint.config.js
.eslintrc.*
.prettierrc*
*.log
*.tgz

# Misc local / OS files
*.DS_Store

# Optional: keep CHANGELOG, README, LICENSE, icon.png (do NOT ignore)
# (Intentionally NOT ignoring: README.md, CHANGELOG.md, LICENSE, icon.png, package.json)

# If a future dist/ or out/ build directory is introduced and you only want lib/:
# out/**

# Prevent accidental inclusion of repository root via symlinks
../**
!../vscode-extension/**

# End of file